               <msContents>
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i1">
                     <rubric>Nomina sacra; the name of the archbishop Qerǝllos and of the bishop Ṗeṭros; the name of the donor (?) and other individuals.&#xD;
A few lines (2 or 4) on the incipit page of Texts I, II, and IV (alternating with black lines for Texts I and IV); two lines of the incipit of Texts III and V; initial lines of some sections in Text I and of some paragraphs in Text IV; some words in “Tǝmḫǝrtä ḫǝbuʾat” (Text II); directives for the ministers; titles of Biblical books; words: ʾardǝʾǝt in Text I, ʾab, dǝngǝl and eṗṗes qoṗṗosat in Text IV. Abbreviations; some notes in the margins; elements of the punctuation signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals.</rubric>
                     <incipit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </incipit>
                     <explicit>
                        <foreign xml:lang="en"/>
                     </explicit>
                     <note/>
                  </msItem>
                  <!--The data in the items below refers to other items. please remove this items and move the information to the appropriate place.-->
                  <msItem xml:id="ms_i2">
                     <note>- Musical notations are written only on fols. 52ra-52vb (within Text IV).</note>
                     <note>- The name of Wäldä Mikaʾel is written over erasures on fols. 30ra, 30rb.</note>
                     <note>- A chain of black and red right-pointing chevrons is used, at the top and over cols. a and b, as decorative band on the incipit page of Text I; sometimes it (or a chain of black and red dots) is also used as sections divider.</note>
                  </msItem>
